<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,651,1002]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,651,678]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[311,393,651,678]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1965,1990]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[151,1436,1018,1946]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 63. Records of Synthemis campioni." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3352065/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Grande Terre. This species was found in at least 10 localities mainly in the southern half of the island, where the sampling effort was much more intense than elsewhere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,651,1002]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,723,750]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Habitat.</emphasis>
Mountain creeks and streams in forests, but also in large fast-flowing streams in the lowlands. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Synthemistidae" genus="Synthemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="campioni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Synthemis campioni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
avoids ultramafic lands.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,651,1002]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,474,795,822]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Biology and behaviour.</emphasis>
Larvae develop in relatively calm water along the stream banks in places where partly submerged roots of large trees slow the current. Exuviae are found on trunks and boulders 0.2–1.4 m above the water surface. Males patrol stretches of a bank (
<quantity box="[622,714,867,894]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" unit="m" value="18.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="6.0">6–30 m</quantity>
). Mating (2 observations) occurs during flight, 0.7–1.2 m above the water surface, for 20–30 s, along the stretch of the bank that was patrolled by the male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,651,1002]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,281,939,966]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Status.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lieftinck" authorityYear="1971" box="[287,511,940,966]" class="Insecta" family="Synthemistidae" genus="Synthemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="campioni">
<emphasis box="[287,511,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Synthemis campioni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably more widely spread than its known distribution and its populations can be large. As a precaution, we rank it as EN, as only a dozen localities are known.
</paragraph>
